We are excited to announce that Glen Lake Athletics has partnered with FinalForms, an online forms, data management, and communication service.

We are asking that ALL parents of Glen Lake student-athletes register their child(ren) on FinalForms.

Please register at: https://glenlake-mi.finalforms.com, and follow the prompts to create your account, register your student(s), and electronically sign required forms.

Thank you for your assistance in streamlining our paperwork and compliance processes, as well as what will now be our primary mode of communication between the Athletic Department, Coaches, student-athletes, and families.

Additional information can be found on the Glen Lake Athletics website. https://glenlakeathletics.org/

post_text:
SENIOR DRIVE - Because we were unable to have the traditional Senior Walk through the school hallways on the Seniorsâ€™ last day (May 22), they will be honored with a Senior Drive instead! The Drive will take place on Sunday, May 31, beginning at 2:30 PM. This is a community-wide event, thus, all are welcome and encouraged to attend.

A Sheriffâ€™s deputy will lead the Drive from Myles Kimmerly Park on Burdickville Road to Old Settlers Park on Dunns Farm Road, and a school bus will act as the caboose signaling the end of the parade.

Choose a spot to park along the route, and please practice safe distancing at all times and remain in your vehicles.

We encourage everyone to decorate cars, wave signs, use noise makers, play music, display Laker pride, and just celebrate our Seniors from the safety of your vehicles with as much pizzazz as possible.

Please note that this Senior Drive is not intended to replace Commencement, which is still tentatively scheduled to occur outdoors on school campus on June 27. More to follow on that later.

WE ARE...GLEN LAKE! 2ï¸âƒ£0ï¸âƒ£2ï¸âƒ£0ï¸âƒ£ğŸ“âš“ï¸

Good afternoon, Lakers - As noted in last weekâ€™s Frequently Asked Questions message, we have been working on a system to distribute student belongings in a safe and appropriate way. Thank you for your patience and understanding as we worked through the process.

The secondary school is now ready to return student belongings that were stored in any school lockers. An elementary pick-up schedule is still in the works.

Starting tomorrow, Thursday, April 23, and again on Friday, April 24th, families will be able to drive to the school to pick up any student belongings left in lockers. Pick-up at the DOJO doors (Bus drop off) will be from 9 - 12:00 noon on both days for all SECONDARY students/parents who wish to pick up belongings.

In order to practice safe socially distancing, we will ask everyone to remain in their vehicles while belongings are delivered to you at the curb.

Any belongings not retrieved will be stored until the end of the school year when we collect school issued materials.

Thanks so much!

Mrs. Long

post_text:
Glen Lake Families & Community Members,

This week the 5th grade-12th grade choir and music students have been challenged to a new social media challenge. The project is an enjoyable way to get us all singing, which naturally reduces cortisol and boosts endorphins.

To participate in the fun challenge, all you have to do is go outside, sing a song, and then post the video and challenge your friends. Make sure to write the title of the challenge in your video description (OUTDOOR SINGING CHALLENGE) and add the new hashtag (#SingOutside) We would love for you to post your own video and share it to Facebook, Instagram, etc. It takes 5 minutes, it's easy, and fun.

Let's all get creative and enjoy!
text:
Glen Lake Families & Community Members,

This week the 5th grade-12th grade choir and music students have been challenged to a new social media challenge. The project is an enjoyable way to get us all singing, which naturally reduces cortisol and boosts endorphins.

To participate in the fun challenge, all you have to do is go outside, sing a song, and then post the video and challenge your friends. Make sure to write the title of the challenge in your video description (OUTDOOR SINGING CHALLENGE) and add the new hashtag (#SingOutside) We would love for you to post your own video and share it to Facebook, Instagram, etc. It takes 5 minutes, it's easy, and fun.

Let's all get creative and enjoy!
